The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Torture charge
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Torture charge
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	An NRI software engineer visiting his ailing father in the city was arrested on Friday for allegedly torturing his wife mentally and physically.        
	Sudhir Ganguly, the 40-year-old New Jersey resident, was produced before an Alipore court magistrate and remanded in police custody till January 3.        
	Sudhirs wife Madhumita, who returned to the city from the US 18 months ago, lodged a police complaint against him seven days ago.         
	We investigated the complaint and decided to arrest the accused, said an officer of Kasba police station.        
	The couple married in 1999 and have a three-year-old son.        
	Dowry arrest: The husband of a 22-year-old Muchipara homemaker and three of his family members were arrested on Friday for allegedly attempting to kill her after their demand for dowry was not met.        
	The four  Somnath Sonkar, his mother Dharmi Devi, brother Debnath and sister-in-law Swapna  allegedly forced Poonam to drink a bottle of mosquito repellent on Thursday afternoon. Neighbours admitted the homemaker to a local hospital.                                                                                                                                                           
